    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a weird humming sound and the fan wont spin. it sounds like it's trying to start but then just stops. what's probably wrong with it and is it safe for me to look at?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A weird humming sound with a fan that won't spin is a classic sign of a stuck capacitor or a failing motor, but before you touch anything, you must ensure the unit is completely powered off at the breaker, because even a dead capacitor can hold a lethal charge that could shock you or cause a fire if you try to inspect it while the unit is still connected to the grid.\n\nIf you are comfortable with basic electrical work, you can check the capacitor with a multimeter once the power is off, but if you are not an electrician, it is much safer to call a professional, as they have the tools to safely discharge components and diagnose the issue without risking injury.\n\nIn the meantime, you should check the outdoor unit for any obvious obstructions like leaves or debris blocking the fan blades, as a physical blockage can prevent the fan from spinning even if the motor is fine.\n\nIt is also worth noting that if the unit is in a hard-to-reach spot, you might need to climb a ladder or use a step stool, so be very careful with your footing and never lean over the edge of a roof or unstable surface.\n\nIf the problem persists after these checks, it is best to contact a certified HVAC technician",
